section.section:
"County plan" means a comprehensive plan for adequately providing throughout the county, including all towns, municipal corporations, and sanitary districts in the county, the following facilities and services by public or private ownership:
Water supply systems;
Sewerage systems;
Solid waste disposal systems;
Solid waste acceptance facilities; and
Systematic collection and disposal of solid waste, including litter.

text.section:
"Litter" means any:
Waste material;
Refuse;
Garbage;
Trash;
Debris;
Dead animal; or
Other discarded material.

"Multiuse sewerage system" means a sewerage system that:
Serves only 1 lot;
Serves a number of individuals;
Has a treatment capacity of more than 5,000 gallons a day; and
Is not publicly owned or operated.
